## Why This Question Is Asked

This question tests the ability to diagnose gateway-induced tail latency in a multi-region service mesh environment with tenant-specific QoS controls. It evaluates skills in:

- **Observability-driven debugging**: Using metrics, distributed tracing, and packet capture to isolate performance anomalies
- **Understanding QUIC and mTLS internals**: Particularly around stream multiplexing, path MTU discovery, and session resumption
- **Rate limiting architecture**: Per-tenant token bucket behavior under burst conditions
- **Controlled experiments**: Systematically isolating variables to identify root causes

## Key Concepts

- **Per-tenant rate limiting**: Token bucket algorithms that enforce quotas per tenant can introduce bursty traffic patterns when refill rates are misconfigured
- **Cross-region QUIC/RPC latency**: QUIC's stream multiplexing can experience head-of-line blocking at the gateway when streams share a single connection
- **Path MTU discovery**: Cross-region paths may have varying MTUs; fragmentation increases latency and packet loss probability
- **TLS session tickets**: Cached session tickets can cause stalls during rotation or when tickets become invalid

## Code Example

```javascript
// Per-tenant latency statistics collection schema
const tenantLatencyStats = new Map();

function recordLatency(tenantId, latencyMs, region) {
  if (!tenantLatencyStats.has(tenantId)) {
    tenantLatencyStats.set(tenantId, {
      p50: [],
      p95: [],
      p99: [],
      bucketRefills: 0,
      regionLatencies: new Map()
    });
  }

  const stats = tenantLatencyStats.get(tenantId);

  // Record latency by percentile bucket
  if (latencyMs < 50) stats.p50.push(performance.now());
  else if (latencyMs < 200) stats.p95.push(performance.now());
  else stats.p99.push(performance.now());

  // Track region-specific latencies
  const regionStats = stats.regionLatencies.get(region) || [];
  regionStats.push({ timestamp: Date.now(), latency: latencyMs });
  stats.regionLatencies.set(region, regionStats);
}

function analyzeTokenBucketCorrelation() {
  // Correlate latency spikes with token bucket exhaustion events
  return tenantLatencyStats.entries().map(([tenant, stats]) => ({
    tenant,
    refillSpikeCount: stats.p99.length,
    correlation: computeCorrelation(stats.bucketRefills, stats.p99.length)
  }));
}
```

