## Why This Question Is Asked

Diagnosing inter-region TLS latency spikes without code changes tests depth in three critical areas: production observability skills, understanding of certificate handling across geographic boundaries, and knowledge of crypto infrastructure bottlenecks under distributed load.

## Key Concepts

| Concept | Impact |
|---------|--------|
| TLS handshakes | Full handshakes add 1-2 RTTs; resumable sessions reduce this |
| OCSP/CRL fetching | Network path to CA infrastructure adds unpredictable latency |
| Session tickets | Cross-region cache misses force full handshakes |
| ALPN negotiation | Protocol preference mismatch triggers fallbacks |
| HSM signing | Queue buildup during peak loads creates signing stalls |

## Code Example

```javascript
// Measure TLS handshake duration to region endpoints
const tls = require('tls');

function measureHandshake(regionHost) {
  return new Promise((resolve) => {
    const start = Date.now();
    const socket = tls.connect({
      host: regionHost,
      port: 443,
      servername: regionHost.split('.')[0]
    });

    socket.on('secureConnect', () => {
      const duration = Date.now() - start;
      socket.end();
      resolve({ host: regionHost, duration, sessionReused: socket.isSessionReused() });
    });

    socket.on('error', (err) => resolve({ host: regionHost, error: err.message }));
  });
}

// Execute across all regions
Promise.all([
  measureHandshake('use1.example.com'),
  measureHandshake('usw1.example.com'),
  measureHandshake('euw1.example.com'),
  measureHandshake('apne1.example.com')
]).then(console.log);
```

## Quick Reference: Latency Breakdown

| Scenario | Expected Extra Latency | Key Metric |
|----------|------------------------|------------|
| OCSP stall | 100-500ms | LB debug log timestamps |
| Ticket miss | 1 RTT | Session reuse rate |
| ALPN retry | 1-2 RTT | Protocol negotiated |
| HSM queue | 50-200ms | Signing queue depth |

