    connections: 0
  - id: server2
    weight: 2  # 40% traffic
    connections: 0

# Least Connections
active_connections:
  server1: 150
  server2: 100  # Route new requests here

# IP Hash
hash_source: client_ip
modulus: server_count
result: consistent server mapping
```

### Architecture for 100K RPS
```
Internet → CDN → L7 Load Balancer (ALB) → L4 Load Balancer (NLB) → Microservices集群
                                ↓
                          WAF & Rate Limiting
                                ↓
                       Health Checks & Auto Scaling
```

## Performance Considerations
- **Throughput**: NLB handles >100M TPS, ALB handles ~10M requests
- **Latency**: Layer 4 = 1-2ms, Layer 7 = 3-8ms
- **Scaling**: Horizontal load balancer deployment with DNS round-robin

## Implementation Examples
```javascript
// Weighted Round Robin Implementation
class LoadBalancer {
  constructor(servers) {
    this.servers = servers.map(s => ({...s, currentWeight: 0}));
  }

  getServer() {
    const totalWeight = this.servers.reduce((sum, s) => sum + s.weight, 0);
    let best = null;
    let max = -1;

    this.servers.forEach(server => {
      server.currentWeight += server.weight;
      if (server.currentWeight > max) {
        max = server.currentWeight;
        best = server;
      }
    });

    if (best) best.currentWeight -= totalWeight;
    return best;
  }
}
```

## Trade-offs
- **Layer 4**: Max performance, minimal features
- **Layer 7**: Rich features, higher latency
- **Round Robin**: Simple, equal distribution
- **Least Connections**: Better for varied response times
- **IP Hash**: Session persistence, uneven distribution risk

