## Concept
HTTP/2 suffers from head-of-line blocking at the TCP level - a single lost packet blocks all streams. QUIC solves this by using UDP as the transport protocol and implementing reliability, congestion control, and stream multiplexing at the application layer.

## Implementation
```go
// QUIC stream independence
for _, stream := range conn.Streams() {
    go func(s quic.Stream) {
        // Each stream processes independently
        data, err := io.ReadAll(s)
        // Lost packets only affect this stream
        handleStreamData(s.ID(), data)
    }(stream)
}

// Connection-level recovery
conn.HandleLostPackets(func(packetID uint64) {
    // Selective retransmission
    if shouldRetransmit(packetID) {
        conn.RetransmitPacket(packetID)
    }
})
```

## Trade-offs
- **Pros**: Stream independence, faster recovery, reduced latency
- **Cons**: Higher CPU usage, UDP firewall issues, complex implementation
